TY  - JOUR
AU  - Andrews, Isaiah
AU  - Gentzkow, Matthew
AU  - Shapiro, Jesse M.
T1  - Measuring the Sensitivity of Parameter Estimates to Estimation Moments*
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjx023
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 132
IS  - 4
SP  - 1553
EP  - 1592
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We propose a local measure of the relationship between parameter estimates and the moments of the data they depend on. Our measure can be computed at negligible cost even for complex structural models. We argue that reporting this measure can increase the transparency of structural estimates, making it easier for readers to predict the way violations of identifying assumptions would affect the results. When the key assumptions are orthogonality between error terms and excluded instruments, we show that our measure provides a natural extension of the omitted variables bias formula for nonlinear models. We illustrate with applications to published articles in several fields of economics. 
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjx023
ER  - 



